    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD represents the pinnacle of rotary performance, maintained in concours-level condition. The 13B-REW power plant delivers linear thrust through its sequential Hitachi HT12 turbochargers, with a flawlessly functioning charge relief valve and switching actuator system. The five-speed manual gearbox offers crisp synchronizer engagement, transferring torque to the rear wheels via the factory Torsen limited-slip differential. Its lightweight aluminum suspension components and unyielding unibody integrity ensure the razor-sharp turn-in response the FD3S is legendary for. With zero thermal degradation of the cooling system and perfect apex seal integrity, this specimen is mechanically peerless and entirely stock, preserving the original kinematic balance.",
